(5) The claimants shall be intitled,
if they so desire, to be heard by the
Tribunal either in person or by counsel,
and the Tribunal shall be entitled to
call upon the claimants to present such
additional explanations, documents or
arguments as it may think necessary.
(6) Before the hearing of any case
the Tribunal shall require from the
parties a deposit or security for such
sum as it may think necessary to cover
the share of each party in the expenses
of the Tribunal. In fixing the amount
of such sum the Tribunal shall base itself
principally on the extent of the land
claimed. The Tribunal shall also have
power to demand a further deposit
from the parties in cases where special
expense is involved.
(7) The honorarium of the arbitrators
shall be calculated per month, and fixed
by the Governments concerned. The
salary of the Secretary and any other
persons employed by the Tribunal shall
be fixed by the President.
(8) Subject to the provisions of this
Annex the Tribunal shall have full power
to regulate its own procedure.
(9) In dealing with the claims the
Tribunal shall take into consideration:
(a) any applicable rules of Interna-

(b) the general principles of justice
and equity;
